snippet: Jo Pavey of Britain won the first major title of her career at 40 in the 10,000 meters at the European championships in Zurich.
abstract: Jo Pavey of Britain wins first major title of her career, at age 40, in 10,000 meters at European championships in Zurich.
lead_paragraph: Jo Pavey of Britain won the first major title of her career at 40 in the 10,000 meters at the European championships in Zurich.

headline.main: Briton Earns First Major Title at 40
